# ECS Module

**Files**: `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/ECS/World.h`, `World.cpp`, `System.h`, `CheckedRegistryAccessor.h`
**Namespace**: `pg`

---

## Module Purpose and Responsibilities

The ECS module provides a data-driven game-object model built on top of [EnTT](https://github.com/skypjack/entt). Its responsibilities are:

- Own the single `entt::registry` and `entt::dispatcher` instances for the application.
- Register `System` objects and enforce a **one-writer-per-component** invariant at registration time.
- Sort systems into a valid execution order using a **dependency-derived topological sort** before the first frame.
- Drive per-frame updates: dispatcher flush â†’ system updates â†’ event cleanup â†’ deferred-request flush.
- Provide `CheckedRegistryAccessor` as the only sanctioned way for systems to read and write components, enforcing access declarations at runtime.
- Buffer structural registry changes (adds, removes, destroys) so they are applied safely outside of system iteration.
- Implement two distinct event-entity patterns: **deferred events** (visible next frame) and **in-frame events** (visible within the same frame to later-ordered systems).

