## `System` Base Class

```cpp
class System
{
public:
    System() = default;
    ~System() = default;
    virtual void Update(const pg::Timestep& ts) = 0;
    virtual SystemAccessDecl DeclareAccess() const;  // returns empty decl by default
};
```

Every concrete system **must** override `DeclareAccess()`. The default implementation returns an empty `SystemAccessDecl`, which causes every component access inside `CheckedRegistryAccessor` to assert â€” this is intentional, forcing all systems to be explicit about their data dependencies.

Systems are owned exclusively by `World` via `unique_ptr` inside `SystemEntry`. They must not be registered while another system is updating.

