## `SystemAccessDecl` Struct

```cpp
struct SystemAccessDecl
{
    std::unordered_set<std::type_index> readSet;
    std::unordered_set<std::type_index> writeSet;
    std::unordered_set<std::type_index> addSet;
    std::unordered_set<std::type_index> inframeAddSet;
};
```

| Set | Meaning | Access methods gated on it |
|---|---|---|
| `readSet` | Components this system reads (const access). | `view<const C>()`, `get<const C>()` |
| `writeSet` | Components this system mutates in-place. | `view<C>()`, `get<C>()` |
| `addSet` | Components this system **deferred-adds** (next frame). | `emplace_deferred<C>()`, `emplace_oneframe<C>()`, `EmplaceEvent<C>()` |
| `inframeAddSet` | Components this system **in-frame-adds** (same frame, later systems see immediately). | `emplace_inframe<C>()`, `EmplaceInframeEvent<C>()` |

A single component type may appear in both `writeSet` and `addSet` simultaneously (e.g., a system that mutates existing instances and also creates new ones).

`inframeAddSet` participates in topological sort edge generation (see below); `addSet` does not.

