## `CheckedRegistryAccessor` API

Constructed by `World::GetRegistry()` with a reference to the live `entt::registry` and a **copy** of the active system's `SystemAccessDecl`. The copy is intentional â€” it prevents dangling if `m_Systems` is reallocated.

### View

```cpp
template<typename... Components>
auto view();

template<typename... Components, typename... Exclude>
auto view(entt::exclude_t<Exclude...> excl);
```

Asserts that each (non-const-stripped) component type is in `readSet` or `writeSet`, then forwards to `m_Registry.view<Components...>()`. Supports exclusion filters.

### Get

```cpp
template<typename Component>
decltype(auto) get(entt::entity e);
```

Asserts the (non-const-stripped) component type is in `readSet` or `writeSet`, then calls `m_Registry.get<Component>(e)`.

### emplace_deferred

```cpp
template<typename Component, typename... Args>
void emplace_deferred(entt::entity e, Args&&... args);
```

- Asserts `Component` is in `addSet`.
- Heap-allocates a `Component` with the forwarded args.
- Pushes a `DeferredRequest` to `m_DeferredRequests` (applied after all systems update this frame).
- The apply trampoline asserts the entity does not already have `Component` before calling `reg.emplace<Component>`.
- Component becomes visible to systems in the **next** frame.

### emplace_oneframe

```cpp
template<typename Component, typename... Args>
void emplace_oneframe(entt::entity e, Args&&... args);
```

- Asserts `Component` is in `addSet`.
- Pushes a `DeferredRequest` to `m_DeferredRequests`.
- The apply trampoline: emplaces `Component` on the entity, then immediately pushes a **second** deferred request to `m_DeferredOneFrameComponents` that will `remove<Component>` from the entity at the **next** flush.
- Net effect: `Component` is visible for exactly **one** frame (the frame after the call), then automatically removed.
- Used for transient per-entity state flags, e.g., `UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent`.

### emplace_inframe

```cpp
template<typename Component, typename... Args>
void emplace_inframe(entt::entity e, Args&&... args);
```

- Asserts `Component` is in `inframeAddSet`.
- Asserts the entity does not already have `Component`.
- **Immediately** calls `m_Registry.emplace<Component>(e, ...)` â€” no deferral buffer involved.
- The component is visible to all systems that execute **after** the calling system in the same frame.
- Note: the current implementation has a bug â€” it references `ent` (undefined) instead of the parameter `e` in the pre-condition assert. This does not affect the emplace itself.

### EmplaceEvent

```cpp
template<typename Component, typename... Args>
void EmplaceEvent(Args&&... args);
```

- Asserts `Component` is in `addSet`.
- Creates a new entity via `m_Registry.create()`.
- Pushes a `DeferredRequest` that will attach both `pg::EventComponent` and `Component` to that entity.
- The event entity becomes visible in the **next** frame and is automatically destroyed by `ClearEvents()` at the end of that frame.
- Use this when a system needs to broadcast a typed event to other systems.

### EmplaceInframeEvent

```cpp
template<typename Component, typename... Args>
void EmplaceInframeEvent(Args&&... args);
```

- Asserts `Component` is in `inframeAddSet`.
- Creates a new entity via `m_Registry.create()`.
- **Immediately** emplaces both `Component` and `pg::EventComponent` on the new entity.
- The event entity is visible to all systems running **after** the calling system in the same frame, then destroyed by `ClearEvents()` at frame end.
- Used for render commands: e.g., `DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent`, `DrawQuadInFrameEvent`.

### destroy_deferred

```cpp
void destroy_deferred(const entt::entity& e);
```

Pushes the entity to `m_DeferredDestroys`. The entity is destroyed at the end of the frame after all deferred emplaces are applied.

### remove_deferred

```cpp
template<typename Component, typename... Args>
void remove_deferred(entt::entity e, Args&&... args);
```

Heap-allocates a `Component` instance constructed from the forwarded `args` (the constructed value is never used â€” the apply trampoline only calls `reg.remove<Component>(ent)` and discards it). The allocation exists purely for type-erasure: the `DeferredRequest` stores typed destroy/apply function pointers. No declaration check is performed on removal â€” any system may remove any component type. Be aware that `Component`'s constructor **will** execute with the forwarded args even though the resulting object is thrown away.

### Entity Lifecycle

```cpp
entt::entity create();
void destroy(entt::entity e);  // immediate â€” use only when safe (not during iteration)
```

`create()` and `destroy()` are immediate pass-throughs. `destroy()` without the `_deferred` suffix should only be used when no active iteration over that entity's components is in progress.

### Non-Access Queries

```cpp
bool valid(entt::entity e) const;

template<typename... Components>
bool any_of(entt::entity e) const;

template<typename... Components>
bool all_of(entt::entity e) const;
```

These three methods carry no declaration assertions and pass through directly to `entt::registry`.

