## Non-Obvious Design Decisions and Invariants

### Accessor Holds a Copy of the Decl

`GetRegistry()` copies the `SystemAccessDecl` into the returned `CheckedRegistryAccessor` rather than storing a reference into `m_Systems`. This prevents a dangling-reference bug if `m_Systems` were ever reallocated (e.g., a future `RegisterSystem` call mid-update would be caught by the `m_ActiveSystem` assert, but the defensive copy costs nothing at frame rate).

### `addSet` Does Not Generate Sort Edges

Deferred adds are invisible within the same frame regardless of system execution order. Generating edges for them would create spurious ordering constraints and could introduce artificial cycles. Only `writeSet` and `inframeAddSet` generate edges.

### Deferred-Destroy Is Applied After Deferred-Emplace

Within `FlushDeferredRequests()`, one-frame component emplaces run first, then persistent emplaces, then destroys. This ordering means a system can emplace a component and destroy the entity in the same frame â€” the emplace runs first (which may be a no-op since the entity is about to be destroyed) and the destroy runs last. The validity check (`m_Registry.valid(op.entity)`) inside the flush guards against operating on already-destroyed entities.

### One-Frame Components Use a Two-Stage Deferred Chain

`emplace_oneframe` does not schedule a simple timed remove. Instead, its apply trampoline â€” executed at flush time â€” immediately pushes a second `DeferredRequest` into `m_DeferredOneFrameComponents`. This second request removes the component at the **next** flush. The effect is: the component lives exactly one flush cycle after the frame it was requested in.

### `GetRegistryDirect` Is Gated on `TESTS_ENABLED`

Direct registry access bypasses all declaration enforcement. It is excluded from production builds to ensure that only tested, declaration-compliant paths exist in shipping code.

### Registration Guards Iterator Validity

`RegisterSystem` asserts `m_ActiveSystem == nullptr` and `m_Sorted` is set to `false`. This means the sort is not triggered immediately; it is deferred to the next `Update()` call. Calling `RegisterSystem` and then immediately querying `World::GetRegistry()` outside of an update would assert.

### `emplace_inframe` Bug Note

The current implementation of `emplace_inframe` in `CheckedRegistryAccessor.h` (line 124) references the identifier `ent` in its double-add assertion, which is not defined in the method's parameter list (the parameter is named `e`). This causes a compile error when the assertion is enabled. The emplace itself on line 128 correctly uses `e`. This is a latent defect.

### EnTT `dispatcher` Is Flushed Before Systems

`m_Dispatcher.update()` runs at the very start of `Update()`, before any system executes. This ensures that EnTT signal-based subscribers (if any) receive their callbacks before the system update loop for the same frame.
